{"sequence":58,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:52:02.777153976Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-211fa9f9","body":"finding_summary: The new pending-mutation marker is written inside `.beads/` but is not ignored, so the repo's standard `git add .beads/` workflow can stage and commit transient dirty-state into source control. severity: high. affected_files: `src/adapters/br_process.rs`, `.gitignore`. remediation_hint: Move the marker outside `.beads/` or add an explicit ignore rule and regression test so `git add .beads/` cannot pick it up. evidence: `src/adapters/br_process.rs:26-28` defines `.beads/.br-unsynced-mutations`, and `src/adapters/br_process.rs:567-576` writes it for every tracked mutation. `.gitignore:24-47` ignores other transient runtime artifacts but has no rule for this file. Once committed, other checkouts/restarts will falsely recover a dirty workspace and block import safety flows until a manual flush clears it.","dedup_key":"be2c6760d1fc9b64cd1f5c2e2a698918e3c9685c6a7fa25475fcb558331d600a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":59,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:52:02.786519175Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-a804e338","body":"finding_summary: `BrAdapter::check_available()` treats any successful spawn of `br --version` as healthy, even when the command exits non-zero, so the new health gate can report `Healthy` when `br` is actually unusable. severity: medium. affected_files: `src/adapters/br_process.rs`, `src/adapters/br_health.rs`. remediation_hint: Require `status.success()` and convert non-zero exits into `BrUnavailable` (or a structured `BrExitError`) so callers get the intended early failure. evidence: `src/adapters/br_process.rs:380-396` ignores the returned `ExitStatus` entirely and returns `Ok(())` after any completed process. `src/adapters/br_health.rs:18-19` and `src/adapters/br_health.rs:66-68` rely on that result to distinguish `Healthy` from `BrUnavailable`, so a broken `br` binary named `br` still passes preflight and only fails later during real mutations.","dedup_key":"dcc31ab17a30058bc3bc4c7542fb13a764b20c1fbbf48fd8ca0005b7d305dcbf","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":60,"timestamp":"2026-04-16T05:52:02.795732087Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-9f03de88","body":"Bug in `exec_tracked_mutation` (src/adapters/br_process.rs:643): the `?` on `self.clear_pending_mutation_marker()?` in the `Err` branch will early-return with a marker-cleanup IO error, masking the original mutation error stored in `result`. When a mutation fails AND the adapter was not already dirty AND marker cleanup fails (e.g. disk full, permissions), the caller receives an IO error about file removal instead of the actual `BrExitError`/`BrTimeout`/etc. Fix: replace `self.clear_pending_mutation_marker()?` with `if let Err(e) = self.clear_pending_mutation_marker() { tracing::warn!(..., \"failed to clear pending mutation marker after failed mutation: {e}\"); }` so the original mutation error is always propagated.","dedup_key":"ffc1078c2a4e172c0c3a6c7822beda94d4ea1e6fa86704f977be1bb56d57eb2e","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260416043549","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
